description.3: Hawkeye vs the Defenders! What has led this super hero team to take on the Avenging Marksman Hawkeye?
description.12: After Victorius kidnaps Bobbi Morse, Ka-Zar goes after him with the Super-Soldier Serum in hand!
description.14: Linda offers her origin story to Ghost Rider, chronicling her rise as Witch-Woman. Still entrenched in her deal with Satan, Ghost Rider has little choice but to turn on a former ally...
description.15: A rescue mission extracts General Ross from his Russian captors- but will Glenn Talbot now take Ross' place? Hulk successfully reaches New York's shores...and must immediately help Hawkeye with the ever-shocking Zzzax!
description.16: The Iron Playboy is trapped in the Masked Marauder's clutches, but after a surprise turn around Iron Man defeats the Masked Marauder and Steel! But at what cost?
description.18: Return of the 4-D Man! And this time, Mercurio brought an army! Will Thor and company be trapped in the mines of the Dark Nebula?
description.20: Vampire lovers unite! A WHOLE series dedicated to tales of blood-sucking foes!
description.21: Warlock's teenage companions reveal that they are targets of discrimination. After the teens are placed in protective custody, Warlock decides to free his friends despite protests from Von Doom. Plus, Reed Richards takes on Doctor Doom of Counter-Earth, but this time, the roles are reversed!
description.22: The Shaper of Worlds has re-written reality! The FF can't make heads or tails of this strange, new world hatched from the mind of a crazed villain. Plus, there's no sense to be had with the Wild Ones brainwashing the team!
description.23: Spider-Man meets Power Man! Following Gwen Stacy's funeral, J. Jonah Jameson solicits Luke Cage for his services; to capture Spider-Man dead or alive.
description.24: Wanda is hurt by her brother's protests against her love affair with Vision. After storming out of Avengers Mansion, she is retrieved by Swordsman's partner, Mantis. With the current roster depleted, the Swordsman and Mantis are given a second chance to join the team of heroes. But will the two scoundrels prove their worth?
description.25: Cap is at the mercy of Nightshade and her werewolf army!
description.26: Daredevil and Black Widow vs. Stilt-Man! Will their heroic team-up save California from becoming the next Atlantis?
description.27: Black Widow’s back! And just in time too- Daredevil and Widow must take out Angar the Screamer before he drives all of San Francisco mad! But when Widow falls under the Screamer’s spell, will DD lose his comrade in arms?
description.29: Doctor Strange at last finds the Ancient One - being held captive by the forces of Shuma-Gorath!
description.30: Hulk's been shanghaied into Captain Omen's crew, but will he wriggle his way free? If Hulk doesn't get himself out of this bind quickly, he could forever remain on the ocean floor!
description.31: It's iron versus steel in this action-packed issue! Iron Man takes on the Steel, but little does he know, villains seldom work alone! Enter: The Masked Marauder!
description.33: The Sssth Lizardmen have taken Asgard! Will Thor be able to free his fellow Asgardians from bondage?
description.34: The First Appearance of Blade, The Vampire Slayer! Will Blade be able to work alongside the vampire hunters or will his lone wolf attitude get the best of him?
description.35: Having escaped Gideon's clutches, the Fantastic Four must now take on the Wild Ones Gang! But how does Slugger Johnson fit into this madness? And finally, an ending where the FF don't win!
description.37: The Death of Norman Osborn.  It's the Green Goblin's last stand as Spider-Man seeks vengeance for the death of Gwen Stacy.
description.38: After an image of the Scarlet Witch and Vision embracing goes viral, the Avengers receive more hate mail than ever. Turns out, "normal" folk are offended by a romance between a sentient robot and a mutant. The Avengers are attacked by the "Living Bombs", a group of extremists who believe the Avengers are destroying American values.
description.39: Cap and the Falcon throw down with the Serpent Squad!
description.40: Captain Marvel takes the fight to Titan! Will he be able to defeat the multi-powered Super-Skrull!
description.50: The TOMORROW WAR reaches its thrilling climax! Spider-Man and his group of freedom fighters are still outgunned, but the heroes have a powerful trump card up their sleeve: Enter BLACK BOLT, and the mysterious INHUMANS!
description.53: Daredevil’s back in San Francisco and all is not well. Suffering from hallucinations, DD fears that he may have cracked at long last. But is there a more sinister force behind these mind games?
description.54: The Death of Gwen Stacy!  Read the most heart-wrenching moment in Amazing Spider-Man history as Gwen Stacy dies!
description.55: The Avengers Mansion is stormed by Africa-American protesters who believe Black Panther has "sold-out to the white establishment." The mob is organized by a mysterious man known as the Lion God, a mythic hero from Africa who wants Panther to return to his African roots.
description.56: Captain America is thrown into a hallucinatory prison that he cannot escape!
description.57: Where General Ross is in hot water with the Russians, the Hulk is in cold water- literally! While trying to cross the Arctic Ocean, Hulk requires an assist from one Captain Omen. But is Omen as benevolent as he seems?
description.58: Tony Stark and Pepper Potts are ambushed while on a business trip to Detroit. Taking them hostage Firebrand demands Tony to bring Iron Man to Simon Gilbert's grave! What could Firebrand be plotting? What does Simon Gilbert have to do with anything?
description.60: What strange forces have driven Balder insane? Upon his return to Asgard, Thor finds that all Asgardians are missing...and in their stead- Lizardmen from beyond the stars!
description.62: Warlock walks straight into a trap set by Astrella. There, Warlock encounters the Brute, a former human trapped in a monster's body. When Warlock discovers a way to revert the Brute to human form, his true identity is revealed. Introducing Reed Richards of Counter-Earth!
description.63: Reed, Sue, Franklin and Medusa have been kidnapped by mad scientist Gregory Gideon! But for what purpose? If the Human Torch doesn't arrive soon, it could be a disastrous ending for Marvel's First Family!
description.66: While Gemini and Lord Plunder manage to escape, Professor Conrad takes the Super-Soldier Serum and transforms into VICTORIUS!
description.72: The TOMORROW WAR rages on! With Iron Man trapped in the future, Spidey needs to find reinforcements, and who better to answer the call than the HUMAN TORCH! Best hero buddies, together again!
description.73: Doctor Strange is under mystical attack! Desperate to prove his strength over the Sorcerer Supreme, Cyrus Black casts illusions splitting the Defenders into chaos. Will Strange see through the machinations of Black's mind? Or will another Defender rise to save the day?
description.74: Linda Littletrees becomes Roxanne’s savior when she delivers a life-saving antidote. Snake Dance’s worshippers may have turned on their master, but a life still hangs in the balance! The true face of Witch-Woman is revealed.
description.76: In the not too distant future, Martians have invaded the Earth, and nearly destroyed humanity. Only one man can still stand up and fight their dominance -- KILLRAVEN!
description.77: Daredevil and Black Widow are greeted by Hawkeye upon their return from battling the Dark Messiah. This time, Clint Barton won't leave San Francisco until Natasha agrees to rekindle their romance.
description.78: Doctor Strange embarks on his own to Stonehenge to confront the Shuma-Gorath threat face-to-face.
description.82: On Spider-Man's partner menu today...the Invincible IRON MAN! Join Peter and Tony on a crazy trip through time...into the TOMORROW WAR!
description.88: Spider-Man's throwdown with the Hulk brings General Ross to town!
description.89: Magneto is holding the X-Men and most of the Avengers captive. The Master of Magnetism reveals his plans to create a nuclear army of brainwashed mutants. Plus, the Black Widow becomes an official member of the Avengers team, when it's up to her to save the day.
description.90: Who is Dr. Faustus' prisoner and why is Captain America so shocked?!
description.91: The Ever Lovin' Blue-Eyed Thing arrives for a knock-down drag-out fight with Captain Marvel!
description.92: What is the secret of Seacliff House?
description.93: General 'Thunderbolt' Ross and Hulk, captives of the Gremlin! Kidnapped by the Russians, Bruce Banner and Ross have no choice but to forge an alliance. But where Banner agrees to cooperate...the Hulk refuses!
description.94: Iron Man's back's against the ropes as he faces the Mandarin and the Unicorn dead on! If he can't stop them, its death for all!
description.96: What's gone awry with Balder? Plus, Thor's battle with the Rock Trolls heats up, as the other heroes of Earth rally to help.
description.98: What's happened to Agatha Harkness? The FF answer a distress call, only to find Agatha's home destroyed. Meanwhile, Franklin's behavior raises red flags for Sue, but there's no time to act- the Dragon Man attacks!

3.text: Hawkeye vs the Defenders! What has led this super hero team to take on the Avenging Marksman Hawkeye?

5.text: Namor is called to defend an underwater realm once again - but this time, it's NOT Atlantis? Who are the mysterious Zephyreans?

6.text: Enter Nekra, the Priestess of Darkness…and the sister of Mandrill!

7.text: While on assignment in San Francisco, Spider-Man is attacked by the accursed Werewolf by Night! Under the mind-altering enchantment of an evil mage, Jack Russell tries to rip the Friendly Neighborhood Web-Head to shreds!

10.text: While Luke Cage was off fighting Spider-Man, a new villain emerged in New York City! Enter Chemistro, the inventor behind the alchemy gun! Cage is hired to defeat this new foe, but Chemistro won’t retire easily!

11.text: The Kale family rescues Man-Thing, (and New York City), when the swamp monster starts running rampant on unfamiliar streets. But how did Florida native Man-Thing end up in New York? Joshua Kale reveals the origins of the Tome of Zhered-Na. Will Dakimh abandon his quest at long last?

12.text: After Victorius kidnaps Bobbi Morse, Ka-Zar goes after him with the Super-Soldier Serum in hand!

13.text: Jack accidentally unleashes the Krogg from a cave, and the two battle across the forest!

19.text: Dracula sets his eyes on the group of malevolent bikers who wronged him! He will finally have his revenge!

27.text: Black Widow’s back! And just in time too- Daredevil and Widow must take out Angar the Screamer before he drives all of San Francisco mad! But when Widow falls under the Screamer’s spell, will DD lose his comrade in arms?

29.text: Doctor Strange at last finds the Ancient One - being held captive by the forces of Shuma-Gorath!

34.text: The first appearance of Blade, The Vampire Slayer! Will Blade be able to work alongside the vampire hunters or will his lone wolf attitude get the best of him?

37.text: John Romita masterfully conveys Spidey's sadness and rage in this cover. And that text? No lie. Gobby's going down.

41.text: Left to drown in a tunnel by Señor Suerte, Luke Cage breaks free at the very last minute! Determined to make Señor Suerte pay, Cage tracks the villain down to his secret hideout. But the Señor is ready for the attack…and has planted a series of gambling related traps! Luke Cage vs. the Wheel of Fate!

42.text: Robert Walton and cabin boy Sean are pulled from the ice by Frankenstein’s Monster. The creature continues his tale, this time recounting his brush with death at the hands of savage tribesmen. The Arctic tundra swallows all alive.

43.text: Can the Werewolf make it through the circus’ other beats before he can even face Swami Rihva?

44.text: Reprinting Avengers (1963) #62: Black Panther vs. Man-Ape!

46.text: From the strange future of 2018, he is…Killraven! Jonathan Raven, gladiator and crusader, is kidnapped alongside his crew of rebels to perform feats of glory in the Martian’s arena!

47.text: Dr. Nemesis may hold the antidote to return Ant-Man to human size! Guest-starring the Avengers!

49.text: The final showdown between Namor and Doctor Hydro is here at last! Can the prince of the blood defend his realm from catastrophe? And the ancient legend of Atlantis continues!

53.text: Daredevil’s back in San Francisco and all is not well. Suffering from hallucinations, DD fears that he may have cracked at long last. But is there a more sinister force behind these mind games?

54.text: The death of Gwen Stacy. 'Nuff said.

61.text: Dracula is recovered by a fisherman in the town of Liverpool and brought inside a church. Can the Lord of Vampires escape the hallowed ground to continue his reign of terror?

64.text: Luke Cage is fed up with fending off thugs on the late Frank Jenks account, so he decides to dig deeper into Frank’s personal affairs. An illegal casino operator named Señor Suerte learns of Cage’s probing, and decides to silence Cage no matter the cost!

65.text: Is the entire planet possessed? It sure seems that way, as violent outbreaks continue to plague Earth’s population. All trails lead to the Florida Everglades and the Kale family. Who is Dakimh the Enchanter? What talisman does he require of Jennifer? Plus, Man-Thing vs. Mongu!

66.text: While Gemini and Lord Plunder manage to escape, Professor Conrad takes the Super-Soldier Serum and transforms into VICTORIUS!

69.text: Namor and Namorita continue their fight against Doctor Hydro - as the villain attacks Atlantis! Plus, an untold tale of the ancient history of Atlantis!

70.text: The misogynist Man-Bull feels the wrath of The Cat after the brute lashes out in a bar!

71.text: Shanna’s upscale dinner with her jungle cats goes horribly awry when the mind-enslaving Mandrill shows up for the main course! Mandrill’s first appearance!

72.text: The TOMORROW WAR rages on! With Iron Man trapped in the future, Spidey needs to find reinforcements, and who better to answer the call than the HUMAN TORCH! Best hero buddies, together again!

75.text: Jack Russell has been kidnapped by the mystic Swami Rihva, who has thrown the Werewolf into a cage for the world to see!

76.text: In the not too distant future, Martians have invaded the Earth, and nearly destroyed humanity. Only one man can still stand up and fight their dominance -- KILLRAVEN!

77.text: Daredevil and Black Widow are greeted by Hawkeye upon their return from battling the Dark Messiah. This time, Clint Barton won't leave San Francisco until Natasha agrees to rekindle their romance.

78.text: Doctor Strange embarks on his own to Stonehenge to confront the Shuma-Gorath threat face-to-face.

81.text: Namor faces off against Doctor Hydro! To the victor - the life of Namorita!

83.text: Ant-Man, who is still stuck at the size of an actual ant, fights for survival against two deadly foes: his mutant wife…and a tabby cat!

84.text: When the hermit-millionaire Luthor Kane hold Jack’s sister hostage, the hairy horror storms the millionaire’s mansion!

85.text: Luke Cage breaks into the Baxter Building, but the Fantastic Four are at the ready! A battle ensues, but once Cage explains his mission to receive payment from Dr. Doom, Reed Richards gives him an aircraft to fly to Latveria! Cage embarks on his quest to Castle Doom.

86.text: Elizabeth Frankenstein, wife of Victor, succumbs to the wrath of her husband’s creation. Victor pays the ultimate price. Will the monster have his way?

97.text: Quincy Harker has poisoned Dracula with a wooden dart. Desperate to be free from the pain, Dracula seeks out Heinrich Mortte, a doctor with a terrible secret. Discover the secret here!
